</ul>

<p>
  I'm a freelance web developer working primarily in the Ruby
  ecosystem. I write a lot of open source code you can find on github
  speak as at as many meetups and conferences as I can. I'd like to
  learn Haskell/Clojure/Erlang to compliment Ruby's
  object-orientated side. While I'm not programming hopefully I'm
  in a new country with some banging trance pumpin' through my
  headphones.
</p>

<p>
  I'm the author of the most popular and indepth resources on
  <a href="/2012/07/advanced_caching_revised/">caching in rails applications</a>.
  I'm writing a comprehensive book on <a href="2013/07/announcing-high-performance-rails/">application performance</a>.
  I offer <a href="/performance-consultations">performance consultations</a> for who need to faster apps.
  and <a href="/on-site-services">on site services</a> for people who work better in person.
  I enjoy travelling and speaking at conferences and local events.
  Hopefully you'll find me on the road in 2014 talking about these important <a href="/conference-circuit/2014">topics</a>.
</p>

